Delete in a Splay Tree using the Top-Down-Join Approach:
Found the subject?
1. Splay the subject (Make the subject the root).
2. Delete the subject. It will possibly give two subtrees.
Two subtrees:
3. Splay the maximum key on the left subtree (Make it the root).
4. Join the right subtree as a right child of this new root.
5. Done. This is our final tree.
No left subtree?
3. The right subtree is the final tree.
No right subtree?
3. Still, splay the maximum key on the left subtree (Make it the root).
4. Done. This is our final tree.
Did not find the subject?
1. Splay the parent (The node we accessed last while searching for the subject).
2. Done. This is our final tree.
